article.headline: Arkansas State 86, Arkansas Tech 74
article.story: JONESBORO, Ark. (AP) -- Adrian Banks and Isaac Wells both scored more than 20 points Saturday to lead Arkansas State to a comeback win over Arkansas Tech. Arkansas Tech (2-6), a Division II school, led by as much as 15 points in the first half, and was still up 34-32 at intermission. But the Wonder Boys lost their shooting touch in the second half. They dropped to 30 percent after making 42 percent of their shots from the field in the first half. The Indians (5-7) took advantage, grabbing the lead for good on a 3-pointer by Ryan Wedel that made in 38-36 ASU just over a minute into the second half. From there, they built their lead to as much as 20 points midway through the second period, after a 17-4 run. Banks finished with 22 points and Wells had 21, while Shawn Morgan added 11 for the Indians. But Tech's Terrance Whiters led all scorers, with 33 points, with help from 11-for-11 free-throw shooting in the second half. Brandon Glenn also had 11 points for the Wonder Boys.
